# SPA deep-link fallback for Cloudflare Pages. Cloudflare serves an existing
# static file before applying this catch-all, so the crawlable public shells the
# build generates (dist/index.html, dist/pricing/index.html, dist/features/...,
# etc.) are served as-is, while any other deep link (/admin, /app, /owner,
# /s/:slug, ...) falls back to the SPA shell so client-side routing can take over.
